SNS -
  SNS is fully managed service that enables the decoupling of microservices.
  SNS is used
  1) Is used to send notification (email, SMS, PUSH)
  2) trigger workflows (via Lambda, SQS, HTTP endpoint)
  3) FAN out a message to multiple destination at once.

Real-World Purpose of SNS:
Purpose                                           Explanation                                                
|----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| ğŸ”” **Alerting / Notifications**     | Send alerts to teams (email/SMS) when errors, failures, or thresholds are hit |
| âš™ï¸ **Event-Driven Workflows**       | Trigger Lambda or SQS when events happen (e.g., new file in S3)               |
| ğŸš€ **Fan-out to multiple services** | Send one message â†’ multiple systems (e.g., email + queue + Lambda)            |
| ğŸ“¢ **Broadcasting messages**        | Send common messages to many subscribers (e.g., push to all devices)          |
| ğŸ” **Decoupling systems**           | Allows services to talk to each other **without tight coupling**              |


